# Terminal Game Engine

A lightweight C++ engine for building text adventure games.  

## Features

- **Easy to use node editor**  
  Make complicated and diverse games with the simple node editor.
  
- **Automatic Exporting Games**  
  Export your game to play with the Engine Runner

- **Handles in-game variables and conditionals**  
  Use variables and conditionals to make any game logic

## Installation

Clone the repository:

'''bash
git clone https://github.com/findof1/Terminal-Game-Engine.git
cd Terminal-Game-Engine
'''

Create a build directory and run CMake:

'''bash
mkdir build
cd build
cmake ..
'''

Build the project:

'''bash
cmake --build . --config Release
'''

Notes:
- Make sure your environment paths include any required DLLs on Windows (e.g., SDL3, GLFW).
- EngineCore is built as a shared library and automatically linked to EngineGUI.
- You can add your own runner by creating a new executable that links to EngineCore if needed.

